Every Kalmykia resident is a debtor
Residents of the republic increasingly visit the official website of the Russian Federal Service of Court Prosecutors for Kazakhstan.
According to the experts of the department of organizational control, informatization and information security of the republican department, over the past eight months, more than 140 thousand visits were registered to the site itself, more than 42 thousand - to the section "Bank of data of executive proceedings", 661 payment receipts about debt payment were downloaded.
According to the chairman of the Public Council under the Federal Social Security Administration of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan, Valery Bogdanov, almost every resident of the region has debts for utilities, GIDDD fines, bank loans, loans, and no one is insured against unforeseen situations.
However, debtors may face negative consequences, such as being banned from travelling abroad.
That is why the Russian Federal Civil Service Commission for Kazakhstan recommends that all those who plan to travel abroad should check with the local court bailiffs or on the website www.r08fssprus.ru for information on the existence of unpaid debts and to pay them off.
The service created the "Data Bank of executive proceedings" for the convenience of citizens.
This special electronic application is available not only on the regional websites of the Russian Federal Customs Service, but also on social networks and mobile devices such as iPads, iPhones and smartphones.
The data bank contains information about the executive proceedings initiated by Kalmyk prosecutors against all debtors, - explains the assistant of the head of the Russian Federal Customs Service for Kazakhstan Delgir Bodgayeva.
"When there are debts, the system displays information about the number and date of the executive proceedings; the name of the body that issued the executive sheet or other act; its number, the amount and the type of debt; the address of the court officers' department; the F.I.O. of the executing court officer; the contact telephone.
Information on the progress of the executive proceedings can also be obtained on the portal of state services at the address: http://epgu.gosuslugi.ru"
